brainly_data.question: What happens if the Senate and House of Representatives pass two different bills on the same topic? (3 points) The conference committee will meet and resolve the bills' differences. Advisors to the president will meet with the sponsors of the proposed bills. The Senate version of the bill will take precedence and go to the president. Congress will meet with the president to agree on one or the other bill.
brainly_data.subject: History
